column5: Just got back from spending a week up at Callendar with the family. Fishing was up and down. One day it was jigs the next day it was spinner rigs. The wind made it hard to fish a couple of days. Caught alot of walleye all sizes, biggest was 26incher, also caught some real nice smallies and only 2 sheephead witch is unusual. :dunno:Here are a couple of pics from the week. attachment=19060:cottage 154.jpg  Scooter
Lookin' good Scooter.   It's only been a few weeks and I already miss her
I've never fished Nip in the fall but I think that's going to change this year!!
Scooter  Looks like your young Lad is having Fun!  We will be up there Aug 18.  Rick
He sure did Rick. He loves it up there. Hope you have a great trip in August.  Scooter
Well done! I'm actually fishing CBay right now. Got two nice walleye and a couple huge sheeps.
I marked tons of fish along the big weedline but couldn't get much bite. Scooter
